{"title_page": "Auburn\u2013Clemson football rivalry", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox sports rivalry\n| wide                  = yes\n| name                  = Auburn\u2013Clemson football rivalry\n| image                 = \n| image_size            = \n| caption               = \n| team1                 = [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn Tigers]]\n| team1logo             = Auburn Tigers logo.svg\n| team2                 = [[Clemson Tigers football|Clemson Tigers]]\n| team2logo             = Clemson University Tiger Paw logo.svg\n| sport                 = \n| firstmeeting          = October 28, 1899<br />Auburn 34, Clemson 0\n| mostrecent            = September 9, 2017<br />Clemson 14, Auburn 6\n| nextmeeting           = \n| total                 = 51\n| series                = Auburn leads, 34\u201315\u20132\n| largestvictory        = Auburn, 56\u20130 (1921)\n| longeststreak         = Auburn 14, (1952\u20132010)\n| longestunbeatenstreak = \n| currentstreak         = Clemson 4, (2011\u2013present)\n| currentunbeatenstreak = \n| trophy                = \n| trophy series         = \n| stadiums              =  \n| map_location          = \n| map_width             = \n| map_label1            = \n| map_mark1             = \n| map_label1_position   = \n| coordinates1          = \n| map_label2            = \n| map_mark2             = \n| map_label2_position   = \n| coordinates2          = \n| map_caption           = \n}}\n{{OSM Location map      \n| nolabels = 1  \n| coord = {{coord|33.64|-84.161}}\n| zoom = 6\n| width = 295 \n| height = 250\n| caption = Locations of Auburn and Clemson\n| mark1 = Orange pog.svg\n| label1 = Auburn\n| mark-coord1 = {{coord|32.603|-85.486}}\n| label-pos1 = top\n| label-color1 = black\n| mark2 = Orange pog.svg\n| label2 = Clemson\n| mark-coord2 = {{coord|34.676|-82.836}}\n| label-pos2 = top\n| label-color2 = black\n}}\nThe '''Auburn\u2013Clemson football rivalry''' is an American [[college football]] [[college rivalry|rivalry]] between the Auburn Tigers and Clemson Tigers.\n\n==Series history==\nThe rivalry began in 1899 and was played almost annually up until 1929. It was renewed in 1940 on an annual basis until 1955, with only a three-year break from 1943\u201345 for [[World War II]]. After that, the series became much more intermittent. They have faced each other in two bowl games; the [[1998 Peach Bowl (January)|1998 Peach Bowl]] and the [[2007 Chick-fil-A Bowl]].\n\n==Notable games==\n===1998 Peach Bowl===\n{{Main|1998 Peach Bowl (January)}}\n\n===2007 Chick-fil-A Bowl===\n{{Main|2007 Chick-fil-A Bowl}}\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==Game results==\n{{sports rivalry series table\n| format = compact\n| cols = 2\n| series_summary = yes\n| team1 = Auburn\n| team1style = {{NCAA color cell|Auburn Tigers}}\n| team2 = Clemson\n| team2style = {{NCAA color cell|Clemson Tigers}}\n\n| October 28, 1899 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 34 | Clemson | 0 \n| November 15, 1902 | Auburn, AL | Clemson | 16 | Auburn | 0\n| October 15, 1904 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 5 | Clemson | 0 \n| November 11, 1905 | Auburn, AL | Clemson | 6 | Auburn | 0\n| November 10, 1906 | Clemson, SC | Clemson | 6 | Auburn | 4\n| November 2, 1907 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 12 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 22, 1910 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 17 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 14, 1911 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 29 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 19, 1912 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 27 | Clemson | 6 \n| October 18, 1913 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 20 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 17, 1914 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 28 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 16, 1915 | Anderson, SC | Auburn | 14 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 20, 1916 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 28 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 19, 1917 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 7 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 17, 1919 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 7 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 15, 1920 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 21 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 14, 1921 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 56 | Clemson | 0 \n| September 29, 1923 | Clemson, SC | Tie | 0 | Tie | 0 \n| October 4, 1924 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 13 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 3, 1925 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 13 | Clemson | 6 \n| October 2, 1926 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 47 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 1, 1927 | Clemson, SC | Clemson | 3 | Auburn | 0\n| October 6, 1928 | Auburn, AL | Clemson | 6 | Auburn | 0\n| October 5, 1929 | Clemson, SC | Clemson | 26 | Auburn | 7\n| November 9, 1940 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 21 | Clemson | 7 \n| November 29, 1941 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 28 | #16 Clemson | 7 \n| November 28, 1942 | Auburn, AL | #16 Auburn | 41 | Clemson | 13 \n| November 23, 1946 | Montgomery, AL | Clemson | 21 | Auburn | 13\n| November 22, 1947 | Clemson, SC | Clemson | 34 | Auburn | 18\n| November 27, 1948 | Mobile, AL | #9 Clemson | 7 | Auburn | 6\n| November 26, 1949 | Mobile, AL | Tie | 20 | Tie | 20 \n| November 25, 1950 | Auburn, AL | #11 Clemson | 41 | Auburn | 0\n| November 24, 1951 | Clemson, SC |Clemson | 34 | Auburn | 0\n| November 22, 1952 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 3 | Clemson | 0 \n| November 21, 1953 | Clemson, SC | #14 Auburn | 45 | Clemson | 19 \n| November 20, 1954 | Auburn, AL | #18 Auburn | 27 | Clemson | 6 \n| November 19, 1955 | Mobile, AL | #12 Auburn | 21 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 28, 1961 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 24 | Clemson | 14 \n| October 27, 1962 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 17 | Clemson | 14 \n| October 14, 1967 | Auburn, AL | Auburn | 43 | Clemson | 21 \n| October 12, 1968 | Clemson, SC | Auburn | 21 | Clemson | 10 \n| October 11, 1969 | Auburn, AL | #20 Auburn | 51 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 10, 1970 | Clemson, SC | #9 Auburn | 44 | Clemson | 0 \n| October 23, 1971 | Auburn, AL | #5 Auburn | 35 | Clemson | 13 \n| [[1998 Peach Bowl (January)|January 2, 1998]]<sup>A</sup> | Atlanta, GA | #13 Auburn | 21 | Clemson | 17 \n| [[2007 Chick-fil-A Bowl|December 31, 2007]]<sup>B</sup> | Atlanta, GA | #22 Auburn | 23 | #15 Clemson | 20\n| September 18, 2010 | Auburn, AL | #16 Auburn | 27 | Clemson | 24<sup>OT</sup>\n| September 17, 2011 | Clemson, SC | Clemson | 38 | #21 Auburn | 